                 com.android.volley.Response.ErrorListener errorListener)
                      throws Cannon.NotLoadedException
        CONCENTRATE FIRE AT ZE POINT! FIRE! Fires a multi-part request at the resource point.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of expected response object.
        Parameters:
        classOfResourcePoint - Class of ResourcePoint.
        method - HTTP request method. Refer to Request.Method.
        resourcePathParams - Parameters for populating placeholders in the skeleton resource path.
        requestParams - Request body. If method is GET, provided parameters will be treated as URL. queries and will not be added to the request body but appended to the URL.
        oAuth2Token - OAuth 2.0 token to be inserted into the request header.
        files - Files you want to send. The map should contain the form field name as the entry's key and a android.util.Pair containing the actual File and MIME type string. Refer to android.content.ContentResolver#getType(android.net.Uri).
        successListener - Success Response.Listener.
        errorListener - Response.ErrorListener.
        Returns:
        Returns true if cannon was fired, false if otherwise.
        Throws:
        Cannon.NotLoadedException - OMGZ! ZE CANNON IS NOT ZE LOADED! If the Cannon is not loaded, we can't fire it, can we?
